IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: FILML.A., INC. STREAMLINES AND ENHANCES THE ON-LOCATION FILMMAKING PROCESS FOR COMMUNITIES AND CONTENT CREATORS, TO ENSURE THE GREATER LOS ANGELES ECONOMY CONTINUES TO THRIVE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: FILML.A., INC. STREAMLINES AND ENHANCES THE ON-LOCATION FILMMAKING PROCESS FOR COMMUNITIES AND CONTENT CREATORS, TO ENSURE THE GREATER LOS ANGELES ECONOMY CONTINUES TO THRIVE.
IRS990.Desc: FILML.A., INC. DELIVERED HIGH QUALITY, EFFICIENT PERMITTING SERVICES FOR OVER 6,460 PRODUCTIONS, INCLUDING FILMS, TELEVISION, COMMERCIALS, STILL PHOTOGRAPHY AND STUDENT PRODUCTIONS. SERVICES INCLUDE COORDINATION OF ALL ASPECTS OF FILMING INCLUDING LOCATION SCOUTING, PRODUCTION PLANNING AND ON-LOCATION GOVERNMENT MONITORING (POLICE, FIRE, STREET CLOSURES) FOR PERMITTEES. IN ADDITION, FILML.A., INC. PROVIDED PERMITEE INSURANCE VERIFICATION, COLLECTED AND REMITTED $13.5 MILLION IN FEES TO GOVERNMENT AGENCIES, INCLUDING THE CITY AND COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES, CITY OF SANTA MONICA, LOS ANGELES WORLD AIRPORTS AND 16 OTHER GOVERNMENTAL ENTITIES. IN ADDITION, FILML.A., INC. ISSUED 486 LICENSES FOR FILMING AT SCHOOLS IN THE LOS ANGELES UNIFIED SCHOOL DISTRICT AND TWO OTHER SCHOOL DISTRICTS. SERVICES INCLUDED COORDINATING FILMING, COLLECTING, AND REMITTING $2.9 MILLION IN FEES TO SCHOOLS. THE LOS ANGELES COMMUNITY COLLEGES DISTRICT AND OTHER SCHOOL DISTRICTS WERE INACTIVE IN THE FISCAL YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: FILML.A. INC., PROVIDED SUPPORT SERVICES, INCLUDING NOTIFICATION OF UPCOMING FILMING AND ON-SITE MONITORS FOR PRODUCTIONS. THESE SERVICES ASSIST PRODUCTION COMPANIES IN COMPLYING WITH FILMING ORDINANCES AND MAINTAINING GOOD RELATIONSHIPS WITH NEIGHBORHOODS IMPACTED BY FILMING.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: FILML.A. INC., PROVIDED SUPPORT TO THE FILMING INDUSTRY THROUGHOUT CALIFORNIA BY IMPROVING THE FILMING EXPERIENCE FOR NEIGHBORHOODS IMPACTED BY FILMING THROUGH THE EFFORTS OF THE COMMUNITY RELATIONS DEPARTMENT; DEVELOPING A MODEL FILM ORDINANCE AND WORKING WITH GOVERNMENTAL AGENCIES TO MAKE THEIR COMMUNITIES MORE FILM FRIENDLY; MARKETING FILMING OPPORTUNITIES THROUGHOUT SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA, AND SERVING AS THE PRIMARY SOURCE FOR ALL PUBLIC INQUIRIES RELATED TO FILMING IN CALIFORNIA. FILML.A. COMPILES AND REPORTS PRODUCTION-RELATED DATA AND ANALYSIS FOR GOVERNMENTAL AGENCIES, ECONOMISTS AND THE MEDIA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FILMLA RECOGNIZES THE IMPACT OF TAX POSITIONS IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IF THAT POSITION IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT TO BE SUSTAINED ON AUDIT, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. DURING THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2022, FILMLA PERFORMED AN EVALUATION OF UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AND DID NOT NOTE ANY MATTERS THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OR WHICH MIGHT HAVE AN EFFECT ON ITS TAX-EXEMPT STATUS.

ALL EMPLOYEES RECEIVE SMALL BONUSES FOR EXEMPLARY PERFORMANCE, WHICH ARE INCLUDED IN THE BUDGET THAT IS APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE PRESIDENT'S BONUS IS DETERMINED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE ANNUALLY AS REQUIRED BY HIS CONTRACT. THE CFO/COO'S CONTRACT HAS AN ANNUAL DISCRETIONARY BONUS CLAUSE WHICH IS DETERMINED BY THE PRESIDENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS AN EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE WITH THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE BOARD. THE COMMITTEE IS COMPOSED OF THE FOLLOWING: 1) ED DUFFY, CHAIR 2) BILL ALLEN, VICE-CHAIR 3) SUZANNE HOLLEY, PAST CHAIR 4) MELISSA HARMAN, TREASURER 5) JEAN PREWITT, SECRETARY 6) ELEEN IGE-WONG, AUDIT COMMITTEE CHAIR/BOARD MEMBER 7) ALEX AGUILAR, BOARD MEMBER 8) BENJAMIN EVERARD, BOARD MEMBER 9) MYRA OCAMPO, BOARD MEMBER

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY BOTH THE AUDIT AND FINANCE COMMITTEES OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. FOLLOWING INCORPORATION OF THEIR COMMENTS, THE FINAL DRAFT IS CIRCULATED TO THE ENTIRE BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO SUBMISSION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: QUESTIONNAIRES ARE PROVIDED AT THE BEGINNING OF EACH YEAR FOR DIRECTORS, OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES TO REVIEW AND SIGN. THE AUDIT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD MONITORS THE POLICY REVIEWS ANY CONFLICTS THAT MAY HAVE ARISEN AT EACH OF THEIR MEETINGS DURING THE YEAR. THERE HAVE NOT BEEN ANY CONFLICTS DURING THE YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION OF THE PRESIDENT AND CFO/COO ARE DETERMINED USING INDEPENDENT SOURCES AND OUTSIDE SURVEYS OF SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS AND WITHOUT THE PARTICIPATION OF INTERESTED PERSONS. THE PRESIDENT'S COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS INDEPENDENTLY AND IS EXPRESSLY STATED IN HIS EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT FOR THE TERM OF THE EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT. THE CFO/COO'S COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE PRIOR TO EXECUTION OF HER EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT, BASED ON UPON RECOMMENDATION BY THE PRESIDENT, AND ANY SUBSEQUENT ADJUSTMENTS TO THE CFO/COO'S COMPENSATION DURING THE TERM OF THE EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT ARE AT THE DISCRETION OF THE PRESIDENT, WITHIN THE BOUNDS OF THE INDEPENDENT SOURCES AND OUTSIDE SURVEYS OF SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS. SALARIES FOR ALL "HIGHLY COMPENSATED" EMPLOYEES ARE REVIEWED BY THE PRESIDENT, CFO AND HR DIRECTOR IN COMPARISON TO BENCHMARK SALARY DATA OF FUNCTIONALLY COMPARABLE POSITIONS IN SIMILARLY SITUATED ORGANIZATIONS, BOTH PUBLIC AND PRIVATE (INCLUDING BOTH NOT-FOR-PROFIT AND FOR-PROFIT), AND COMPARABLE LOCATION OF THE ORGANIZATION. DATA IS COMPILED FROM VARIOUS SOURCES INCLUDING GUIDESTAR, HRN PERFORMANCE SOLUTIONS, EMPLOYER'S GROUP, AND THE ECONOMIC RESEARCH INSTITUTE. IN 2022 A COMPREHENSIVE COMPENSATION STUDY WAS CONDUCTED BY A THIRD PARTY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FILML.A., INC. MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND INFORMATIONAL RETURNS AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST. THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE ALSO MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC THROUGH FILML.A.,INC. WEBSITE AT WWW.FILMLA.COM.
